   150	**Recommendation for the merged company.** Combine both frameworks: adopt KBM's multi-dimensional segmentation model (role × sector × geography) as the contact data foundation, and layer Pivot's market-segment dimension (NBD / Venture / Public / Construction Solutions per the merged-company division taxonomy from CRM §3.02 D-3b) as an additional dimension. Required-field validation, duplicate detection, and contact role taxonomy are configured per KBM's specification. Sector classifications follow KBM's list; the specific division names follow whatever the merged-company taxonomy decision in CRM §3.02 D-3b lands on. This combination gives the merged company precise targeting across both how Pivot has organized sales (divisions) and how KBM has organized influencer relationships (role × sector × geography).
   151	
   152	**Decision for the leadership team.** Confirm: multi-dimensional segmentation combining role × sector × geography (KBM framework) + market division (Pivot framework, taxonomy per CRM D-3b). *Recommended default: yes.*
   153	
